The garlicky breadcrumbs gives the pasta an amazing crunch.  It's so good, I always make a little extra to sprinkle on meals throughout the week!

Description:

This recipe works perfectly fine with regular ravioli if you can't get your hands on heart-shaped. It will definitely be delicious no matter what!

ingredients.Name: red pepper flakes, plus more for serving
pecorino romano or parmesan cheese, freshly grated, plus more for serving

directions.Direction: Preheat oven to 250F
Place the peeled garlic in a small oven-proof dish such as a ramekin. Pour in the olive oil and ensure that the garlic is fully submerged (or it will burn).  Add more oil if needed.
Place the dish in the oven and bake for 2 hours or until the garlic turns golden in colour.

Allow the garlic/oil to cool slightly for safer handling.  Separate all but 3 tablespoons of oil from the garlic and save it for another day! It adds wonderful flavour to savoury dishes and is great for making salad dressings. Keep the excess oil in an airtight container in the fridge for up to a few weeks.
Boil the spaghetti according to the directions on the package. Reserve 1/2 cup of the starchy cooking water and drain.
While the pasta is cooking, add the garlic and remaining oil to a large skillet. Heat on medium.

Add the red pepper flakes, reserved pasta water, pecorino romano, and lemon juice.  Continue to heat until the sauce starts to thicken. Gently mash the garlic with a wooden spoon to break it up in the process.
Add the cooked spaghetti and toss to coat it in the sauce. Heat for a little longer if the sauce is too thin.
Season with salt and pepper to your taste.
Serve immediately with more red pepper flakes, cheese, and fresh parsley (if using).  Enjoy!

Creator: kimthefoodie
Name: Garlic Confit Spaghetti
Description:
This garlic confit spaghetti is the gift that keeps on giving because you can use the leftover garlic oil to jazz up other dishes for days!

directions.Direction: Preheat oven to 350F.
Cook the pasta shells according to the directions on the package.
While the pasta is cooking, heat the olive oil in a pan on medium.  Add the shallot and garlic and cook until the shallot is translucent (2-3 minutes).
In a medium sized mixing bowl, combine the shallot/garlic mixture, ricotta, parmesan cheese, egg, basil, salt, and pepper.
Pipe the ricotta mixture into the cooked pasta shells. You'll want to let the shells cool slightly before stuffing them for safe handling.
Spread the marinara sauce on the bottom of a medium-sized baking dish or cast iron pan. Arrange the stuffed shells over the sauce.
Sprinkle the shells with the mozzarella cheese. Cover with foil and bake for 25-30 minutes.  The sauce should be hot and the cheese melted.
Serve with fresh parsley.  Enjoy!

Creator: kimthefoodie

Name: Spicy Parm & Chicken Ditali
Description: Tiny ditali pasta wrapped in a creamy spicy parmesan sauce with seasoned chicken.

ingredients.Name: parmesan cheese, plus more for serving

directions.Direction: Use your hands to roll the Italian sausage meat into one-inch balls. Wetting your fingers will help keep the meat from sticking to your hands.
Heat olive oil in a large skillet over medium. Add meatballs, leaving space in between. Cook on all sides until just browned.
Add garlic and tomato paste. Stir often until the garlic is fragrant.
Reduce heat to medium-low and add pasta, chicken broth, and tomato sauce. Cover until most of the liquid is absorbed into the pasta (about 15-20 minutes), stirring occasionally.
Add parmesan cheese. Stir until the cheese has melted and the sauce is thick and glossy. Season with salt and pepper to your taste.
Serve immediately with more parmesan cheese on top.  Enjoy!

Creator: kimthefoodie
Name: Homemade Spaghettios & Sausage Meatballs
Description: This one pot, homemade version of spaghettios is made with the cutest little mini meatballs!

ingredients.Name: Sliced mushrooms, pepperoni, and cooked bacon for topping

directions.Direction: Preheat oven to 350F.
Spread half of the tomato sauce over the bottom of an oven-safe skillet.
Layer the ravioli over the sauce - It's ok if it overlaps!
Spread the remaining sauce over the ravioli.
Sprinkle mozzarella cheese over the ravioli and add your pizza toppings.
Bake for 25 mins, or until the cheese has melted and the pepperoni edges are crispy.
Top with red pepper flakes (if using). Enjoy!

Creator: kimthefoodie
Name: Canadian Pizza Ravioli
Description: This easy one pan baked ravioli featuring classic Canadian pizza toppings!

ingredients.Name: parmesan cheese, freshly grated (plus more for serving)

directions.Direction: Cook pasta al dente according to the directions on the package.
Meanwhile, melt butter in a large skillet over medium-low heat. Once butter starts to foam, add sage and swirl around until crispy. Remove sage from the pan.
Reduce heat to low. Add garlic and stir frequently until fragrant (1 to 2 minutes).
Add pumpkin, cream, nutmeg, and parmesan cheese. Stir until the cheese has melted and the sauce is smooth. Season with salt & pepper to your taste.
Add cooked pasta to the sauce and toss to coat. Serve immediately with the crispy sage leaves on top. Enjoy!

Creator: kimthefoodie
Name: Creamy Pumpkin Sage Pasta
Description: The cozy, warm flavours of Fall wrapped up the creamiest pasta sauce!

directions.Direction: Cook spaghetti according to the directions on the package. Reserve 1 cup of the starchy cooking water before draining.
In a large skillet, heat butter over medium. Add shallot and cook for 5 to 7 minutes (until golden). Stir frequently.
Reduce heat to low; add brie and cream. Stir occasionally until the brie has melted and the sauce is smooth. Add salt and pepper to your taste.
Add spaghetti to the sauce and toss to coat. If the sauce is too thick, add a splash of the reserved pasta water to loosen it up.
Serve immediately with parsley sprinkled on top, enjoy!

Creator: kimthefoodie
Name: Brie & Shallot Spaghetti
Description: Spaghetti wrapped in a creamy sauce loaded with shallot and rich brie!

ingredients.Name: parmesan cheese, grated (plus more for serving)

directions.Direction: Cook pasta al dente according to the directions on the package.
Meanwhile, heat olive oil in a large skillet over medium. Add garlic, chili flakes, and tomato paste.  Stir frequently until fragrant (2-4 minutes).
Add cream, parmesan cheese, and red pesto. Stir to combine and heat until the cheese has melted and the sauce is thick. Season with salt & pepper to your taste.
Add cooked pasta to the sauce and toss gently to coat.
Serve immediately with more parmesan cheese sprinkled on top. Enjoy!

Creator: kimthefoodie
Name: Spicy Red Pesto Pasta
Description: Pasta in a silky cream sauce made with red pesto.

directions.Direction: Beat eggs in a small bowl. Add breadcrumbs to a separate bowl.
Coat each piece of ravioli in the eggs, then bread crumbs. Shake off the excess after each step.
Place ravioli in a single layer in the basket of your air fryer. Give each piece a light spritz of oil.
Air fry ravioli at 370F for 5 to 6 minutes or until golden brown.
Sprinkle ravioli with Parmesan cheese and parsley and serve with marinara sauce for dipping. Enjoy!

Creator: kimthefoodie
Name: Air Fryer Fried Ravioli
Description: The easiest way to get crispy fried ravioli at home!

ingredients.Name: parmesan cheese, grated (plus more for serving)

directions.Direction: Cook the pasta in a large pot of salted boiling water according to package instructions until al dente. Reserve 1/2 cup of pasta water before draining.
In a large skillet, melt the butter over medium heat. Add the sliced garlic and sauté until fragrant, about 1 minute.
Stir in the nduja, letting it combine with the butter and garlic to form a smooth base.
Reduce the heat to low and add the heavy cream, stirring until combined. Simmer gently for 1–2 minutes, then stir in the Parmesan cheese until the sauce is smooth.
Add the cooked pasta to the skillet, tossing to coat. Use reserved pasta water, a little at a time, to loosen the sauce if needed. Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Serve immediately, topped with extra Parmesan cheese if desired. Enjoy!

Creator: kimthefoodie
Name: Creamy Nduja Pasta
Description: This creamy nduja pasta highlights the bold, smoky-spicy flavour of nduja, a spreadable Italian salami made with pork.

ingredients.Name: (800ml) San Marzano tomatoes with juices, crushed by hand
Freshly grated Parmigiano Reggiano, for serving

directions.Direction: Heat olive oil and butter in a large pot over medium heat. Add the onion, carrot, and celery, cooking until softened (about 7 to 8 minutes). Add the ground beef, breaking it up with a spoon, and cook until browned (about 8 to 10 minutes).
Stir in the tomato paste and cook for 1 to 2 minutes. Pour in the white wine (if using) and simmer until mostly evaporated, scraping up any browned bits from the bottom of the pot.

Add the crushed San Marzano tomatoes with their juices. Season with nutmeg, salt, and pepper. Lower the heat to a gentle simmer and cook semi-covered for 1 hour, stirring occasionally, until the sauce thickens and flavours meld. Add a splash of water if the sauce becomes too thick during cooking.
Stir in the milk and simmer for an additional 10 to 15 minutes. Adjust the seasoning with more salt and pepper if needed.
Toss the sauce with your favourite pasta - I prefer spaghetti. Serve hot with freshly grated Parmigiano Reggiano and enjoy!

Creator: kimthefoodie
Name: Favourite Bolognese
Description: Toss this rich, hearty sauce with spaghetti for a deeply satisfying and flavor-packed meal!

ingredients.Name: dried lasagna sheets, broken into small pieces.

directions.Direction: Heat olive oil in a large pot over medium. Add onion, garlic, Italian seasoning, and tomato paste; stir occasionally until onion is translucent (3 to 4 minutes).
Add ground beef and heat until cooked through. Break it apart into small pieces as it cooks.
Add marinara sauce, chicken broth, and lasagna. Bring to a simmer and stir occasionally until pasta is cooked al dente.
Add cream, basil, and salt & pepper.  Stir to combine.
Divide the soup into bowls and serve with ricotta, mozzarella, and parmesan cheeses on top.
Finish with parsley and red pepper flakes and enjoy!

Creator: kimthefoodie
Name: Easy Lasagna Soup
Description: Everyone's favourite pasta-inspired soup! It's creamy, cheesy and perfectly filling on a chilly day.

directions.Direction: Heat olive oil over medium.  Add onion, carrots, and celery. Add a generous pinch of salt and pepper; stir occasionally for 10 minutes or until the veggies start to soften.
Add garlic and cook for 2 more minutes.
Add chicken broth and bring to a gentle boil. Reduce heat to low and add chicken, bayleaves, rosemary, and thyme. Stir gently to combine.
Cover pot and simmer for 30 to 45 minutes.
Remove bayleaves and herb stems. Add gnocchi and mascarpone cheese. Stir occasionally until the gnocchi cooks through (8-10 minutes).  Season with more salt and pepper to your taste.
Serve immediately and enjoy!

Creator: kimthefoodie
Name: Creamy Gnocchi Chicken Soup
Description: We're taking regular chicken soup up a notch with this one! It's so creamy and thick, it's more like a soup/stew hybrid.

ingredients.Name: all purpose flour (optional, for a thicker soup)
Buffalo style hot sauce (such as Frank’s)

directions.Direction: Heat olive oil in a large pot over medium and sauté the carrot, celery, onion, and garlic until softened, about 5–7 minutes. If using flour, stir it in and cook for 1 minute.

Add the chicken stock and chicken breasts to the pot and season with a generous pinch of salt and pepper. Bring to a boil, then reduce heat to low and simmer until the chicken is fully cooked (internal temperature of 165F), about 15–20 minutes.
Remove the chicken, shred it with two forks, and set it aside.
Stir the cream cheese into the soup until melted and smooth, then mix in the Buffalo sauce and shredded cheddar cheese.
Return the shredded chicken to the pot and season with salt, pepper, and additional Buffalo sauce to taste.
Serve hot, topped with bacon bits, blue cheese, and chopped green onions if using. Enjoy!

Creator: kimthefoodie
Name: Buffalo Chicken Soup
Description: Cozy up with a bowl of creamy buffalo chicken soup that packs just the right amount of kick.

directions.Direction: Preheat oven to 375F.
In a mixing bowl, beat eggs, milk, salt and pepper. Set aside.
Place tortilla in a small round baking dish (6 to 7 inches in diameter. Form a bowl out of the tortilla by crinkling the edges.
Place the the bacon and chives into the tortilla bowl. Pour in the egg mixture and sprinkle cheese over top.
Bake for 20 to 30 minutes, until the eggs have set.
Sprinkle over more chives and slice into four quarters.  Serve and enjoy!

Creator: kimthefoodie
Name: Bacon & Egg Tortilla Quiche
Description: This easy "quiche" for two is equally impressive as it is easy!

ingredients.Name: or 6 stale croissants (can use fresh), sliced into large cubes

directions.Direction: Preheat oven to 375F.
Add the croissant pieces to a large mixing bowl and set aside.
In separate mixing bowl, whisk together the eggs, milk, and half of the cinnamon.
Pour the egg mixture over the croissants and toss them gently to combine. The croissants should soak up most of the liquid. Set aside in the fridge for now.
To a small saucepan, add the butter, brown sugar, honey, and remaining cinnamon. Heat on low until the butter has melted and the sugar has dissolved (about 5 minutes).
Pour the brown sugar mixture into the bottom of an 11x7 inch baking dish.  Spread it out out so that it covers the bottom of the dish in an even layer.
Remove the croissants from the fridge and scatter the pieces over the brown sugar mixture. It's ok if you have to stack some pieces on top of each other.
Cover with foil and bake for 15 minutes. Uncover and bake for another 15 minutes.

Allow the dish to cool long enough to safely handle. Place a large cutting board or baking sheet over the dish and carefully invert it to flip the croissant bake upside down. Tap a few times with your hands until the croissants fall out of the dish.
Take the dish off to reveal the gooey topping!

Creator: kimthefoodie
Name: Sticky Cinnamon Roll Croissants
Description: After accidentally letting a box of croissants go stale, wanted to figure out a way to save them. Inspired by sticky cinnamon buns, this croissant bake has an amazingly gooey brown sugar topping! Of course, fresh croissants work for this too for anyone who is responsible enough to NOT leave them out for too long.

directions.Direction: Using a paring knife, cut a slit into the top rounded edge of the croissant. Carefully pull it open with your hands to make a little boat.
Layer half of the ham over the bottom of the croissant. Add the fried egg and season with black pepper. Place the remaining ham over top of the egg.
Lay the Swiss cheese on top of the croissant and broil on high for 3 to 4 minutes or until the cheese has melted.
Serve immediately with chives and more black pepper on top. Enjoy!

Creator: kimthefoodie
Name: Ham & Swiss Croissant Melt
Description: Here's a breakfast sandwich that's anything but basic. It has ham, egg, and Swiss cheese layered over a sliced croissant that's broiled for an unbelievable melt!

directions.Direction: Heat olive oil in a cast iron pan on medium and add the shallots and veggies. Cook until until veggies have shrunk to half their size.
Meanwhile whisk together eggs, ricotta, Italian seasoning, salt & pepper.
Spread the veggies evenly over the hot skillet and slowly pour the egg mixture over top.
Sprinkle the cheddar cheese over everything and continue to heat the frittata until it's almost cooked through (10-15 minutes).
Pop the frittata under a hot broiler (at least 450F) and heat until the cheese is melted and the top is golden (2-4 minutes).

Creator: kimthefoodie
Name: Ricotta Frittata Loaded with Veggies and finished with cheddar cheese
Description:
With this frittata, ricotta cheese is scrambled right with the eggs to give it this amazing creamy, fluffy texture.

This recipe works well with any thinly sliced vegetables, so feel free to experiment with whatever you have on hand!

directions.Direction: Peel carrots and cut into thick slices.
Boil carrots for 7 to 10 minutes or until fork tender. Strain and return to pot.
Place pot back on the stove and reduce heat to medium. Add butter, brown sugar, and salt.
Stir occasionally until the sauce is thick - about 5 minutes.
Serve immediately with parsley sprinkled on top & enjoy!

Creator: kimthefoodie
Name: Brown Sugar Carrots
Description: These carrots will impress everyone at the table! Smothered in a buttery brown sugar glaze, they make the easiest side.

directions.Direction: Preheat air fryer at 400F.
Cut asparagus spears into thirds. Slice bacon strips into four long pieces (cut in half crosswise, then in half again lengthwise).
Roll up one piece of asparagus with a strip of bacon on a slight angle. Repeat with all 24 pieces.
Pour half of the maple syrup into a small bowl and brush the tops of the bacon wrapped asparagus with it. Air fry for 8-11 minutes or until the bacon is cooked through.
Allow to cool for 5 minutes before handling. Pour the remaining maple syrup into a clean bowl and use a clean brush to spread it over the cooked bites.
Serve and enjoy!

Creator: kimthefoodie
Name: Maple Bacon Wrapped Asparagus Bites (Air Fryer)
Description: An easy 3-ingredient snack to satisfy all your sweet and salty cravings!

ingredients.Name: smoked sausage, such as andouille or chorizo, thinly sliced

directions.Direction: Cook rice according to the directions on the package.
Meanwhile, heat olive oil in a large skillet over medium. Add sausage and stir occasionally until it starts getting crispy (about 5-7 minutes).
Add onion, pepper, garlic, and Cajun seasoning and cook until tender; stirring frequently.
To the skillet, add cooked rice. Stir gently to combine. Add salt and pepper to your taste.
Sprinkle cheddar cheese evenly over rice. Broil on high for 2 to 4 minutes or until the cheese is fully melted.
Sprinkle with parsley and serve. Enjoy!

Creator: kimthefoodie
Name: Cheesy Cajun Sausage & Rice
Description: Who doesn't love an easy skillet recipe?  This Cajun rice is packed with sausage and veggies then topped with melty cheese.  It makes a great side but is also so delicious all on it's own.

ingredients.Name: broccoli florets, chopped into bite sized pieces
cheddar cheese, shredded and divided in half

directions.Direction: Preheat oven to 375°F
Boil the potatoes in a large pot of salted water until fork tender, about 20 minutes. Strain when done.

Meanwhile, bring a pot that has a steamer basket to a boil.  Place the broccoli florets in the steamer basket and steam (covered) for 2 minutes or until the broccoli brightens in colour. If you don't have a steamer, you can drop the broccoli in boiling water for 1 minute and strain immediately.
Place the potatoes in a medium sized bowl and mash them until smooth using a potato masher, or fork (you can also use a food processor or potato ricer for the creamiest result).
Add the butter, cream, half of the shredded cheese, steamed broccoli and salt & pepper to the potatoes and stir until smooth.
Spoon mashed potatoes into a small ovenproof dish or a couple of personal ramekins. Top with the remaining cheese and bake for 10 minutes or until the cheese is melted.
Serve with fresh parsley & enjoy!

Creator: kimthefoodie
Name: Broccoli Cheddar Mashed Potatoes
Description: Using a little (or a lot) of cheese is one of my favourite ways to jazz up potatoes. It may seem over the top, but these cheesy mashed potatoes with broc are made with cream and butter so they’re guaranteed to be amazingly smooth!

ingredients.Name: strips bacon, cooked and chopped into bits
green onion, light green & white parts only, sliced
More bacon bits and sliced green onion for serving (optional)

directions.Direction: Preheat oven to 450F

Prick each potato a few times with a fork and place on a lined baking sheet.  Bake for 45 minutes or until they're soft in the center.  You should be able to pierce each potato with a fork without resistance.
Allow the potatoes to cool long enough for safe handling.  Carefully cut each one in half lengthwise and use a metal spoon to scoop out the flesh.  You should be left with 4 hollow potato skins.
In a mixing bowl, add the potato flesh, butter & cream. Use a potato masher or fork to mash the potaoes until you have a creamy consistency.
Add 2/3rds of a cup of the shredded gouda, plus bacon & chives to the mashed potatoes.  Stir to combine. Add salt & pepper to your taste.
Divide up the mashed potatoes into each of the 4 hollow potato skins.  Place on the same baking sheet with the open side facing up.
Sprinkle with remaining gouda and bake for another 10-15 minutes, or until the cheese on top has melted.
Serve with more bacon bits and sliced green onions on top (optional but highly recommended).  Enjoy!

Creator: kimthefoodie
Name: Bacon & Gouda Twice-Baked Potatoes
Description: A little extra effort goes a long way when it comes to twice-baked potatoes. I love experimenting with different mix-ins & toppings, but this bacon and gouda combo has been a recent fave in my house!

ingredients.Name: dry white wine, such as Sauvignon Blanc or Pinot Grigio

directions.Direction: Cut the French bread loaf in half lengthwise. Place the halves flat-side-up on a baking sheet (or two) lined with parchment paper. Set aside.
In a small bowl, toss 1/2 of the Swiss cheese with the cornstarch. Set aside.
Add the white wine to a saucepan over medium heat. Bring it to a simmer. Gradually add the cornstarch-coated cheese to the wine, stirring constantly as it melts.
Once the cheese is melted, stir in the Dijon mustard.
Carefully spoon the warm cheese mixture over each bread half and spread it out evenly. Sprinkle the remaining shredded Swiss cheese over top.
Broil on high heat (at least 450F) until the cheese is bubbling and the edges of the bread are crispy. Keep a close eye on the bread when it’s under the broiler to avoid burning!
Allow the bread to cool long enough to safely handle. Cut into small slices and serve warm. Enjoy!

Creator: kimthefoodie
Name: Cheese Fondue Bread
Description:
I’m really, really proud of this cheese bread recipe! 

I don’t currently own a fondue pot but I LOVE cheese fondue with bread. This is basically the hand-held version of just that. It’s gooey, creamy, crispy & guaranteed to be everyone’s favourite at the snack table!
Notes: *There are tons of varieties of Swiss cheese like Emmentaler and Gruyere. Any of those cheeses will work well with this recipe. Gouda, while not traditionally Swiss, is also a great option. Use one type on its own or mix them together, it’s up to you!

directions.Direction: Preheat oven to 375F.
Pat salmon dry with a paper towel and transfer to a baking sheet lined with parchment paper. Season salmon with salt and pepper.
In a small bowl combine maple syrup, dijon mustard, smoked paprika, and olive oil. Place half of the mixture in a separate bowl and set aside.
Spoon half of the maple Dijon mixture onto the salmon fillets and rub all over. Top with chopped walnuts.
Bake salmon for 12 to 15 minutes or until cooked through.
Use a clean spoon to drizzle the remaining maple Dijon glaze over the salmon. Enjoy!

Creator: kimthefoodie
Name: Maple Walnut Salmon
Description: Baked salmon smothered in a maple glaze and crusted with walnuts.

directions.Direction: Preheat oven to 375F.
Pat salmon dry with a paper towel and transfer to a baking sheet lined with parchment paper. Season salmon with salt and pepper.
In a small bowl combine dijon mustard and olive oil. Rub all over salmon fillets.
Bake salmon for 12 to 15 minutes or until cooked through.
Serve with dijon butter sauce and fresh parsley. Enjoy!

Creator: kimthefoodie
Name: Baked Salmon with Dijon Butter Sauce
Description: One of the most flavourful ways to do baked salmon!

ingredients.Name: Green onion, thinly sliced, for serving

directions.Direction: In a large bowl, combine miso paste, rice vinegar, garlic paste, honey, and sesame oil.
Slice salmon fillets into one-inch cubes and add them to the sauce. Stir to combine and allow to marinate in the fridge for at least 20 minutes.
Lightly spritz the basket of an air fryer with cooking spray. Arrange the salmon bites skin side down in the basket so they aren’t touching.
Air fry the bites on 400F for 5 to 7 minutes or until the salmon is cooked through.
Sprinkle the bites with sesame seeds and green onion. Enjoy!

Creator: kimthefoodie
Name: Miso Sesame Salmon Bites (Air Fryer)
Description: These bites are light, juicy, and packed with miso sesame flavor! Ready in the air fryer in just minutes, this cooking method will give you tender salmon every single time. These are the perfect addition to a rice bowl or on their own as a snack! I love dipping them in a sweet sauce (like teriyaki) or spicy mayo.

ingredients.Name: Nonstick spray, or oil in a spritzer bottle

directions.Direction: Preheat your air fryer to 370F.
Add the flour and panko bread crumbs each to a separate plate or shallow bowl. Crack the eggs into a separate bowl and beat them.
Add the garlic powder to the breadcrumbs and stir to combine.
Coat each piece of shrimp in the flour, then the eggs, then the breadcrumbs. Shake off the excess after each step!

Place the shrimp in your air fryer and make sure they aren't touching. Give the shrimp a light spritz of oil and air-fry for 6 to 8 minutes, flipping once halfway through cooking. If you have a smaller air fryer, you might have to cook the shrimp in separate batches. Place the shrimp waiting to be cooked in the fridge.
Serve the popcorn shrimp with sweet chili crisp sauce for dipping. Enjoy!

Creator: kimthefoodie
Name: Popcorn Shrimp with Sweet Chili Crisp Sauce
Description: Crispy air fryer popcorn shrimp with a sweet and spicy sauce for dipping!

ingredients.Name: pizza dough (equivalent to about half of a pizza)

directions.Direction: Preheat oven to 450F.
Dust a large work surface with flour. Roll or stretch out the pizza dough into a circle about 10 inches wide.
Drizzle half of the olive oil over the dough and spread it around with a clean hand. Fold the circle in half, drizzle the remaining oil over top, and spread it around again.
Place the crust on a baking sheet or pizza stone and bake for 10-15 minutes or until it turns golden around the edges. Set aside while you prepare the chicken parm toppings.

Creator: kimthefoodie
Name: Chicken Parm Pizza Sandwich
Description: When I saw the viral pizza sandwich I knew I had to give it a try!  This version is stuffed with crispy air fried chicken cutlets, marinara sauce, and melty mozzarella cheese.

directions.Direction: Take one slice of bread and spread the cream cheese over it in an even layer. Sprinkle over the jalepeno pepper, bacon & cheddar cheese.
Place the other slice of bread on top to form your sandwich. Butter the outside of each slice.
Heat a frying pan on medium and add the sandwich. Cook on each side for about 6 minutes, or until the bread is golden and the cheese has melted.
Allow to cool for a couple minutes before handling. Enjoy!

Creator: kimthefoodie
Name: Jalepeno Popper Grilled Cheese
Description: An ooey, gooey grilled cheese sandwich loaded with cream cheese, bacon, and jalepeno!

ingredients.Name: pizza dough (equivalent to about half of a pizza)

directions.Direction: Preheat oven to 450F.
Dust a large work surface with flour. Roll or stretch out the pizza dough into a circle about 10 inches wide.
Drizzle half of the olive oil over the dough and spread it around with a clean hand. Fold the circle in half, drizzle the remaining oil over top, and spread it around again.
Place the crust on a baking sheet or pizza stone and bake for 10-15 minutes or until it turns golden around the edges. Set aside while you prepare the Philly Cheesesteak toppings.

Creator: kimthefoodie
Name: Philly Cheesesteak Pizza Sandwich
Description: Indulge in the ultimate comfort food fusion with this Philly Cheesesteak Pizza Sandwich! Combining savory Philly cheesesteak flavors with a fun (and easy) pizza sandwich crust, this is a guaranteed crowd-pleaser.

ingredients.Name: Ciabatta sandwich bun, sliced in half & toasted
roasted red peppers, the equivalent of about 1 pepper (see below for homemade recipe)
mozzarella cheese, or about 30 grams shredded

directions.Direction: Place the bottom half of the Ciabatta bun on a baking sheet lined with parchment. Spread with sun dried tomato pesto.
Layer on the roasted red peppers, prosciutto, provolone, and mozzarella cheese. Broil in the middle rack on 400F for 3 minutes or until the cheese has melted.
Top the melt with red pepper flakes and a drizzle of honey, if using. Finish with the other half of the bun.
Slice in half diagonally and enjoy!

Creator: kimthefoodie
Name: Prosciutto & Roasted Red Pepper Melt
Description: After I made this sandwich for the first time, I realized how much the toppings resemble what I would normally include on a charcuterie board - in the best way! The sweet roasted red peppers complement salty prosciutto perfectly. I also enjoy adding a little drizzle of honey for added sweetness and flavour. And this wouldn't be a "melt" without the cheese! I used both mozzarella and provolone which make this sandwich oh so gooey!

ingredients.Name: Ranch or blue cheese dressing, for serving

directions.Direction: Heat a large pan over medium and add Buffalo sauce and butter.
Once the butter has melted, add shredded chicken and toss to coat it in the sauce.
Heat a separate pan over medium. Working in batches, lay the tortillas in the pan in a single layer.
Sprinkle a large pinch of cheese over each tortilla and cover the pan until the cheese has melted.
To assemble the tacos, add a spoonful of buffalo chicken to each tortilla and top with chives and ranch or blue cheese dressing. Enjoy!

Creator: kimthefoodie
Name: Easy Buffalo Chicken Tacos
Description: These tacos are extra easy to throw together thanks to store-bought rotisserie chicken.

ingredients.Name: boneless skinless chicken breasts (about 2), cut into one inch cubes
Kosher salt and pepper, to taste
Nonstick spray, or oil in a spritzer bottle

directions.Direction: Preheat your air fryer to 390F.
Season the chicken cubes with a generous amount of salt and pepper.
Add the flour and panko bread crumbs each to a separate plate or shallow bowl. Crack the eggs into a separate bowl and beat them.
Add the garlic powder to the breadcrumbs and stir to combine.
It's time to bread your chicken! Coat each bite in the flour, then the eggs, then the breadcrumbs. Shake off the excess after each step!

Place the chicken bites in your air fryer and make sure they aren't touching. Give the bites a light spritz of oil and air-fry for 10-12 minutes (or until they reach an internal temperature of 165F), flipping once halfway through cooking. If you have a smaller air fryer, you might have to cook the bites in separate batches. Place the bites waiting to be cooked in the fridge.
Add the chicken bites to a bowl and toss them with the garlic butter and parmesan. Enjoy!

Creator: kimthefoodie
Name: Garlic Parmesan Chicken Bites (Air Fryer)
Description: Chicken bites so crispy you'd swear there we deep fried!  These are tossed in a buttery garlic sauce and parmesan for the ultimate flavour.

ingredients.Name: boneless skinless chicken breasts (about 2), cut into one  inch cubes
Kosher salt and pepper, to taste
Nonstick spray, or oil in a spritzer bottle

directions.Direction: Preheat your air fryer to 390F.
Season the chicken cubes with a generous amount of salt and pepper.
Add the flour and panko bread crumbs each to a separate plate or shallow bowl. Crack the eggs into a separate bowl and beat them.
Add the smoked paprika and garlic powder to the breadcrumbs and stir to combine.
It's time to bread your chicken! Coat each bite in the flour, then the eggs, then the breadcrumbs.  Shake off the excess after each step!

Place the chicken bites in your air fryer and make sure they aren't touching.  Give the bites a light spritz of oil and air-fry for 10-12 minutes (or until they reach an internal temperature of 165F), flipping once halfway through cooking. If you have a smaller air fryer, you might have to cook the bites in separate batches. Place the bites waiting to be cooked in the fridge.
Add the chicken bites to a bowl and toss them with the honey chipotle sauce.  Sprinkle with a little flaky salt (if using). Enjoy!

Creator: kimthefoodie
Name: Crispy Honey Chipotle Chicken Bites (Air Fryer)
Description: This is my go-to method for crispy & juicy chicken bites in the air fryer every time.  The smoky honey chipotle sauce is so easy to throw together and tastes WAY better than takeout.

ingredients.Name: neutral high smoke point oil, such as canola
red wine, or sub beef broth

directions.Direction: Preheat oven to 275F
Pat the beef dry with a paper towel and season generously on all sides with salt & pepper.

Heat the oil over medium-high in a Dutch oven. Add the beef and cook for about one minute on each side. The goal is to give it a nice golden brown crust.  Remove the roast from the dutch oven and set aside for now.
Add the shallots, carrots, and tomato paste to the Dutch oven. Stir occasionally until the veggies start to get some colour (3-4 minutes).
Sprinkle the flour over the veggies and stir for 1 minute.
Pour in the wine and use a wooden spoon to scrape the brown bits off the bottom of the pot. Continue to stir until most of the wine has evaporated.
Return the roast to the Dutch oven and pour in the beef broth and worcestershire sauce.  Nestle the herbs into the liquid.
Cover and roast in the oven for 2-3 hours or until the beef pulls apart easily.
Allow the pot roast to rest for 10 minutes.  Pull the beef apart with two forks and serve with the veggies and sauce over mashed potatoes. Enjoy!

Creator: kimthefoodie
Name: The Ultimate Pot Roast
Description: Seriously, this is the only pot roast recipe you'll ever need. It's tender, saucy, flavourful, and goes perfectly with mashed potatoes!

ingredients.Name: olive oil, plus more if needed
boneless skinless chicken breast, sliced lengthwise into 1/2 inch thick strips
pesto, divided (can be homemade or storebought)

directions.Direction: In a large cast iron skillet, heat olive oil on medium. Add chicken and sprinkle it with the salt, pepper, and garlic powder. Stir to coat the chicken in the spices. Heat chicken pieces on each side for 3 to 4 minutes, or until the strips are cooked through.

Remove chicken from the pan and set aside on a plate for now. Drizzle a little more olive oil into the pan if needed, then add garlic, mushrooms, and zucchini. Sauté for 5 to 6 minutes, or until the veggies are tender and slightly golden.
Turn off the heat. Add chicken back into the pan and toss to combine with the veggies.
Add 1/4 cup of the pesto and stir to combine.
Sprinkle the shredded cheese over the entire skillet and broil on high for 3 to 5 minutes or until the cheese has melted.
Using a small spoon, dollop the remaining pesto over the warm skillet and gently spread it around. Top with grated parmesan cheese and red pepper flakes. Serve and enjoy!

Creator: kimthefoodie
Name: Pesto Chicken Skillet
Description: Chicken and veggie skillets are a big weeknight staple for me because they're so easy to whip up.  This recipe features juicy seasoned chicken, sliced veggies, pesto, and a little cheese - perfect as a meal on it's own or served with pasta or rice!

ingredients.Name: boneless skinless chicken breasts (about 2), cut into one inch cubes
Kosher salt and pepper, to taste
Nonstick spray, or oil in a spritzer bottle

directions.Direction: Preheat air fryer to 390F.
Season chicken cubes with smoked paprika and a generous amount of salt and pepper.
Add the flour and panko bread crumbs each to a separate plate or shallow bowl. Crack the eggs into a separate bowl and whisk until beaten.
Coat each chicken piece in the flour, then the eggs, then the breadcrumbs. Shake off the excess after each step!

Place the chicken bites in your air fryer and make sure they aren't touching. Give the bites a light spritz of oil and air-fry for 10-12 minutes (or until they reach an internal temperature of 165F), flipping once halfway through cooking. If you have a smaller air fryer, you might have to cook the bites in separate batches. Place the bites waiting to be cooked in the fridge.
Add the chicken bites to a bowl and toss them with the Nashville hot honey sauce. Enjoy!

Creator: kimthefoodie
Name: Nashville Hot Honey Chicken Bites (Air Fryer)
Description:
These chicken bites encompass everything I love about a Nashville hot chicken sandwich - they're spicy, smoky and amazingly crispy! 

Of course, I had to add honey to the sauce because I'll take any excuse to make something sweet and salty. The end result did NOT disappoint.

ingredients.Name: Kosher salt and pepper, to taste
Non stick spray, or oil in a spritzer bottle
Red pepper flakes, optional for serving

directions.Direction: Chop the cooked bacon into very fine crumbs and add them to a plate or shallow bowl. Pour in the Panko breadcrumbs and stir to combine.
Add the flour to a separate plate. Crack the egg into a separate bowl and beat with a fork.
Season the chicken tenders with a generous amount of salt and pepper.
It's time to bread your chicken! Coat each tender in the flour, then the egg, then the breadcrumb/bacon mixture. Shake off the excess after each step.

Place the chicken in your air fryer and make sure they aren't touching. Give the strips a light spritz of oil and air-fry for 10 to 12 minutes (or until they reach an internal temperature of 165F), flipping once halfway through cooking. If you have a smaller air fryer, you might have to cook the chicken in multiple batches. Place the chicken waiting to be cooked in the fridge.
Add the chicken tenders to a bowl and toss them with the maple barbecue sauce. Sprinkle with red pepper flakes (if using). Enjoy!

Creator: kimthefoodie
Name: Maple BBQ Bacon Chicken Tenders (Air Fryer)
Description: These crispy chicken tenders have bacon bits mixed right into the coating for smoky bacon flavour in every bite!

ingredients.Name: to 4 chicken thighs (bone in, skin on)
kosher salt, plus more to taste

directions.Direction: Preheat oven to 400F.
Trim excess fat from chicken thighs and pat dry with a paper towel.
In a small bowl, combine 2 tbsp olive oil, dijon mustard, salt, and oregano. Rub all over the chicken thighs.
Heat the remaining olive oil in an oven-safe skillet over medium. Add the chicken thighs skin-side-down and cook undisturbed for 5 to 7 minutes or until most of the fat from the skin has rendered.

Flip chicken and add smashed garlic, lemon juice and chicken broth to the pan. Transfer skillet to the oven and cook for 25 to 30 minutes, or until the chicken has reached an internal temperature of 165F.
Remove chicken from the liquid and place skillet back on the stove over medium heat.
Mix flour and softened butter into a smooth paste. Add mixture to the cooking liquid and whisk until the sauce has thickened.  Season with salt to your taste.
Spoon sauce over the chicken thighs, sprinkle with parsley, and serve.  Enjoy!

Creator: kimthefoodie
Name: Lemony Chicken Thighs
Description: Juicy chicken thighs with crispy skin smothered in a tangy lemon butter sauce.

directions.Direction: Preheat air fryer to 400F.
Pat chicken wings dry with a paper towel. Add them to a large bowl and sprinkle with salt, pepper, and paprika. Toss to coat wings in the spices.
Sprinkle wings with baking powder and cornstarch. Toss until they are evenly coated.
Place wings in the air fryer basket and cook for 10 minutes. Flip and cook for another 6-10 minutes. Total cooking time required will vary depending on the size of the wings.
Toss wings in the honey buffalo sauce and serve. Enjoy!

Creator: kimthefoodie
Name: Crispy Air Fryer Wings with Honey Buffalo Sauce
Description: This is my go-to recipe for the CRISPIEST air fryer wings! Tossed in homemade honey buffalo sauce…you can’t go wrong.

ingredients.Name: all purpose flour (can sub gluten free flour)
Boursin, garlic and fine herbs flavour

directions.Direction: Season chicken cutlets on all sides with a generous amount of salt and pepper.
Add flour to a plate. Fully coat cutlets in flour and shake off any excess.
Heat olive oil in a large skillet over medium. Add chicken cutlets in batches to avoid overcrowding the pan. Heat on each side for 5 to 6 minutes or until fully cooked through.
Set cooked chicken aside on a plate and remove any excess fat from the pan.  Return pan to the stove over low heat.
Add cream and Boursin. Stir occasionally until the Boursin has almost fully melted.
Add spinach and stir until occasionally until wilted. Transfer cooked chicken back into the pan. Spoon cream sauce over the chicken and serve. Enjoy!

Creator: kimthefoodie
Name: Boursin Chicken with Spinach
Description: Thinly sliced chicken cutlets smothered in a 3-ingredient Boursin and spinach cream sauce.

directions.Direction: Score the top of the brie wheel and place in an oven-safe dish. Bake uncovered on 375F for 15 minutes or until the center is melted.
Meanwhile, slice 3 jalapenos lengthwise, clean out the seeds and white parts, and cut into thin slices.
In a small pan, heat honey, apple cider vinegar, and jalapeno peppers on medium.
Bring to a boil and bubble for 10 minutes or until the mixture starts to thicken.  It will start to take on a syrupy consistency.
Remove from heat - the mixture will thicken more as it cools.
Pour the candied jalapenos over the Brie and top with sesame seeds and chili flakes (if using). Enjoy!

Creator: kimthefoodie
Name: Candied Jalapeno Baked Brie
Description: This candied jalapeno baked brie will definitely win over everyone at your next dinner party.  It's sweet, spicy, & amazing gooey!

ingredients.Name: 100g pickled sliced jalepeno peppers, plus  cup of the brine.
large bag corn chips (at least 400 grams)
Optional garnishes & dips: Sliced fresh jalepeno peppers, diced red onion, cilantro, lime wedges, salsa, sour cream

directions.Direction: Preheat oven to 350F
Pat the chicken breasts dry with a paper towel and sprinkle with the salt, pepper, cumin, & chili powder. Rub the spices around to coat all sides of the chicken.

Heat the olive oil over medium in a cast iron pan or oven-safe skillet. Add the chicken and sear on each side until golden (about 4 minutes per side). Set aside on a plate for now. Note that they will not be fully cooked at this point!
Add the onion and tomato paste to the same pan. Cook until softened, stirring frequently.
Pour in the pickled jalepeno peppers and chicken broth.  Bring to a gentle boil.
Carefully nestle chicken back into the pan. The tops of the chicken shouldn't be fully submerged in the liquid.
Place the pan in the oven and braise (uncovered) for 30-40 minutes, or until the chicken reaches an internal temperature of 165F.

Transfer the chicken to a cutting board and separate the onions and jalepenos from the remaining liquid (a metal strainer comes in handy here). Save that delicious, briney broth to use for another day. I personally love using it to give my rice or quinoa a kick!
Once it's cool enough to handle, slice the chicken into thin strips.
Spread the corn chips evenly over two or three baking trays (or just do multiple batches).  Sprinkle with cheddar and Monterey jack cheese.
Scatter the chicken slices, plus the cooked onions and jalepenos over each tray.
Bake for 10 minutes or until the cheese has melted.
Serve with any of the optional garnishes or dips listed.  Enjoy!

Creator: kimthefoodie
Name: Jalepeno Chicken Nachos
Description:
These nachos have next level-flavour thanks to the addition of jalepeno braised chicken breasts.  Using pickled jalepeno peppers (brine included), adds an amazing salty kick to the chicken!  Plus, the low & slow braising process guarantees your chicken won't dry out.

Yeah, these take a little longer to throw together than your typical nachos, but you just can't rush perfection sometimes!!

ingredients.Name: strips bacon, cooked and finely chopped

directions.Direction: If time permits, allow your brie wheel to sit out on the counter 1 hour before starting this recipe.
Preheat oven to 350°F
Using a sharp knife, carefully score the top of the brie wheel (cut a criss-cross pattern into it). Place the brie into a small ovenproof dish, cut side-up.
Sprinkle the walnuts over the brie. It's okay if a few pieces fall down into the side of dish!
Bake uncovered for 20 minutes or until the cheese is completely melted in the middle.
Immediately after removing the cheese from the oven, sprinkle it with the bacon and then pour over the maple syrup.
Serve immediately with baguette or crackers. Enjoy!

Creator: kimthefoodie
Name: Maple Bacon Baked Brie with Walnuts
Description: Baked brie is one of those appetizers that doesn’t last long on the snack table (at least at my place lol). This maple bacon baked brie with walnuts is such an awesome combo of salty and sweet that you could serve it as an appetizer, snack or even dessert!

ingredients.Name: Flour, for sprinkling your work surface
Coarse sea salt, for sprinkling the pretzels

directions.Direction: Preheat oven to 400F and line two large baking sheets with parchment paper.
Place the pizza dough on a floured surface and divide it into four equal sections.
Roll each section into ropes about one inch thick. Cut each rope into nuggets, one inch wide.
Combine the water and baking soda in a large pot and bring to a rolling boil.

Boil the dough bites in small batches (5 to 6 at a time) for one minute and remove with a slotted spoon. It's very important to avoid boiling the bites for too long because they'll take on too much of the baking soda flavour - not tasty!
Place the bites on the prepared baking sheet at least 1 inch apart. Sprinkle each bite with a pinch of the coarse sea salt and bake for 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Allow to cool for at least 5 minutes and serve warm with beer cheese dip. Enjoy!

Creator: kimthefoodie
Name: Easy Pizza Dough Pretzel Bites
Description:
Learn how to turn pre-made pizza dough into soft pretzel bites giving it a quick baking soda bath!

Crispy on the outside, chewy on the inside, and perfect dipped in homemade beer cheese!

directions.Direction: Melt the butter over medium heat in a small saucepan or skillet. Add the flour and stir occasionally for 5 minutes or until golden.
Reduce heat to low and add the beer. Stir to combine.
Pour in the cream and stir until the mixture is smooth.
Mix in the dijon mustard, onion powder, garlic powder, and smoked paprika.
Add the cheddar cheese. Stir until the cheese has melted and the sauce is smooth and creamy.  Add salt & pepper to your taste.
Pour the dip into a bowl and serve with soft pretzel bites, bread, chips, or whatever else you’re feeling! Enjoy!

Creator: kimthefoodie
Name: Creamy Beer Cheese Dip
Description: Warm beer cheese perfect for dipping soft pretzels, chips, bread, veggies…you get the idea!

directions.Direction: Preheat oven to 350F.

First, prepare your bread boat by slicing a one-inch layer off the top of the loaf of bread. Using a sharp paring knife, create a "box" with your bread by cutting down to create a rectangle. Be careful to leave at least one inch of bread at the bottom and on all sides of the loaf.  Using the knife or your hands, hollow out the loaf by removing the bread in pieces. Place the bread boat into a large baking dish. Save the bread scraps to make croutons or breadcrumbs!
Pat chicken breasts dry with a paper towel and season with a generous amount of salt and pepper.
Heat 2 tbsp olive oil in a large skillet and place the chicken in the skillet. Cook the chicken breasts for 5 minutes per side and transfer them to a plate.
Reduce heat to medium-low. Drizzle the remaining olive oil into the skillet and add the garlic and sun dried tomatoes. Cook, stirring, for 1 minute or until the garlic is fragrant.

Add the heavy cream and chicken broth and bring to a light bubble. Nestle the chicken breasts back into the skillet and cover.  Cook for 10-12 minutes, or until the chicken reaches an internal temperature of 165F.
Transfer the chicken from the skillet to a cutting board.
Add the parmesan cheese and basil to the liquid, and continue to cook, uncovered, until thick.
Meanwhile, shred the chicken in to smaller pieces with two forks.
Layer the shredded chicken into the bottom of the bread boat. Pour the cream sauce over the chicken and sprinkle over the mozzarella cheese.
Bake for 10-12 minutes or until the cheese is melted.
Sprinkle the bread boat with parsley flakes (if using) and allow it to cool for 2 to 3 minutes before slicing. Enjoy!

Creator: kimthefoodie
Name: Marry Me Chicken Bread Boat
Description: Warning: you might need to knife and fork this because of how amazingly creamy the filling is! Completely worth it though I promise.

ingredients.Name: hot pepper spread (such as Calabrian pepper spread)
Neutral oil with a high smoke point, for frying (such as peanut)

directions.Direction: Lay one egg roll wrapper flat on your work surface with a corner pointing towards you. It should look like a diamond.
Spoon one teaspoon of hot pepper spread in the center of the wrapper. Drag the spread with the back of the spoon to make a smear about two inches wide.
Place one feta cheese stick horizontally over the spread so that the short edges point towards the side corners of the wrap.

It's time to wrap the egg roll! Fold the bottom corner of the wrap over the fillings. Use your fingers to pinch down the sides of the wrap to create a seal beside each end of the feta. Fold the left and right corners of the wrap over the fillings and press gently to seal.

The egg roll should look like an opened envelop. Whisk together the egg and water in a small bowl.  Brush a small amount of egg wash over the top corner of the wrap and roll the egg roll upwards to close it.  Press to seal gently with your fingers.
Repeat Steps 1 to 5 until you have made 12 rolls.
Fill a heavy bottomed pot with one inch of oil and heat to 370F.

Fry the egg rolls for 2 to 3 minutes or until golden, flipping halfway through cooking. You may need to fry the rolls in batches depending on size of your pan. Place the fried rolls on a plate lined with paper towel and allow them to cool for at least 5 minutes.
Serve the egg rolls with honey for dipping. I love warming my honey by heating it over the stove on low for a few minutes. Enjoy!

Creator: kimthefoodie
Name: Spicy Feta Egg Rolls
Description: These bites are made with egg roll wrappers and shallow fried to crispy perfection. I love serving these with warm honey for a sweet and spicy snack!

ingredients.Name: Kosher salt and pepper, to taste
Non stick spray, or oil in a spritzer bottle

directions.Direction: Place the cornflakes in a freezer bag and seal, making sure you squeeze out most of the air.  Crush the cornflakes into fine crumbs using a rolling pin. Add them to a plate or shallow bowl.
Add the flour to a separate plate. Crack the egg into a separate bowl and beat with a fork.
Season the chicken tenders with a generous amount of salt and pepper.
It's time to bread your chicken! Coat each tender in the flour, then the egg, then the cornflake crumbs. Shake off the excess after each step.

Place the chicken in your air fryer and make sure they aren't touching. Give the strips a light spritz of oil and air-fry for 10 to 12 minutes (or until they reach an internal temperature of 165F), flipping once halfway through cooking. If you have a smaller air fryer, you might have to cook the chicken in multiple batches. Place the chicken waiting to be cooked in the fridge.
Add the chicken tenders to a bowl and toss them with the honey sriracha sauce. Sprinkle with chives and sesame seeds. Enjoy!

Creator: kimthefoodie
Name: Honey Sriracha Chicken Tenders (Air Fryer)
Description: These sauced-up chicken tenders are the best combination of crispy, spicy, and sweet!  Made in the air fryer, they're an easy way to cook crispy "fried" chicken at home.

ingredients.Name: prepared marinara sauce, plus more for dipping
mozzarella cheese sticks or cheese strings, halved
Cooking spray or neutral oil loaded into an oil spritzer

directions.Direction: Place the pepperoni in a single layer in the basket of an air fryer.  Air fry at 370F for 5 minutes (or until the edges are crispy). Do this in multiple batches if needed.
Lay one egg roll wrapper flat on your work surface with a corner pointing towards you. It should look like a diamond.
Spoon one tablespoon of marinara sauce in the center of the wrapper. Drag the sauce with the back of the spoon to make a smear about two inches wide.
Place one half of a cheese stick horizontally over the sauce so that the short edges point towards the side corners of the wrap.

It's time to wrap the egg roll! Fold the bottom corner of the wrap over the fillings. Use your fingers to pinch down the sides of the wrap to create a seal beside each end of the cheese. Fold the left and right corners of the wrap over the fillings and press gently to seal.

The egg roll should look like an opened envelop. Whisk together the egg and water in a small bowl.  Brush a small amount of egg wash over the top corner of the wrap and roll the egg roll upwards to close it.  Press to seal gently with your fingers.
Repeat Steps 2 to 6 until you have made 12 rolls.
Place the rolls in the basket of your air fryer (in bacthes if needed). Give the tops a light spritz of oil. Air fry for 6 to 8 minutes or until golden - flipping once halfway through.
Allow to cool for at least 5 minutes. Serve with marinara sauce for dipping and enjoy!

Creator: kimthefoodie
Name: Easy Pepperoni Pizza Rolls (Air Fryer)
Description: Crispy bites of pizza goodness made easy in the air fryer!

ingredients.Name: mini flour tortillas, about 7 inches wide
Optional garnish: fresh parsley and red pepper flakes

directions.Direction: Preheat your air fryer to 360F.
Lay one tortilla on a plate.  Spread half of the pesto on top. Sprinkle half of the mozzarella cheese in an even layer over the pesto.
Place the second tortilla over the cheese and spread with the remaining pesto.
Place the tortilla into the basket of your air fryer and sprinkle with the remaining cheese.
Air-fry for 5 minutes or until the cheese on top is bubbly.
Place onto a cutting board and sprinkle with parsley and red pepper flakes (if using). Use a pizza cutter to slice it into 4-5 pieces.

Creator: kimthefoodie
Name: Tortilla Pesto Cheesy Bread (Air Fryer)
Description: A quick and easy air fryer snack inspired by the tortilla garlic bread trend.

directions.Direction: Preheat oven to 375F.
In a small oven-safe dish, combine the tomatoes, garlic, olive oil, salt, and pepper. Roast uncovered for 30 minutes or until the the skins on the tomatoes have burst.

Score the top of the brie wheel and place in a separate oven-safe dish. After the tomatoes have been roasting for 10 minutes, place the brie in the oven and bake uncovered for 20 minutes or until the center is melted. The tomatoes and brie should come out of the oven around the same time!
Spoon the roasted tomatoes and garlic over the baked brie. Drizzle with balsamic glaze and serve immediately with fresh baguette or crackers. Enjoy!

Creator: kimthefoodie
Name: Baked Brie with Roasted Tomatoes & Garlic
Description: Gooey baked brie with roasted tomatoes, garlic, and a drizzle of balsamic glaze.  I love serving this with fresh baguette!

directions.Direction: Preheat oven or barbecue to 375F.
Using a spatula, spread cream cheese into the bottom of a 13-inch cast iron skillet.
Pour salsa over cream cheese and spread into an even layer.
Sprinkle on corn, black beans, and the cheeses.
Bake (or grill, if using barbecue) for 20 to 30 minutes, or until the cheese on top is melted and bubbling around the edges.
Serve with tortilla chips and enjoy!

Creator: kimthefoodie
Name: 5 Layer Dip
Description: A simple, cheesy dip perfect for enjoying with friends and family on the patio!

directions.Direction: Preheat oven to 450F.
Spread hazelnut spread onto the bottom of a 13-inch cast iron pan.
Arrange milk chocolate chunks in an even layer over the spread.
Cover chocolate with a single layer of marshmallows.
Bake for 5-7 minutes or until the marshmallows are slightly golden.
Serve with graham crackers or fruit for dipping. Enjoy!

Creator: kimthefoodie
Name: Baked Hazelnut S'mores Dip
Description: There's no campfire required to make this version of s'mores!   Made with chocolate hazelnut spread, this s'mores dip goes perfectly with graham crackers and fruit.

directions.Direction: Preheat oven to 375F.
Heat a skillet over medium and add butter. Once butter is foamy, add peaches and cinnamon.
Cook peaches until slightly golden, stirring occasionally.
Turn off the heat and add honey. Stir until the honey and butter are combined and thick like syrup. Set aside.
Score the top of the brie wheel and place in an oven-safe dish. Bake uncovered for 20 minutes or until the center is melted.
Top baked brie with grilled peaches. Sprinkle with basil and serve immediately with bread for dipping.

Creator: kimthefoodie
Name: Grilled Peach Baked Brie
Description: Gooey baked brie topped with sweet grilled peaches. The grilled peach topping is also fantastic served over ice cream!

ingredients.Name: parmesan cheese, grated (plus more for serving)

directions.Direction: Combine all ingredients in a small bowl.

Creator: kimthefoodie
Name: Canadian Pizza Sliders
Description: Sliders with classic Canadian pizza toppings, garlic butter, and a sweet secret ingredient.

ingredients.Name: grilling steak, such as striploin or ribeye

directions.Direction: Cut steak in to bite-sized cubes and pat dry with a paper towel.
Add steak to a mixing bowl and toss with olive oil, salt, and pepper.
Preheat air fryer to 400F.  Arrange steak bites in a single layer in the air fryer basket.
Air fry for 8 to 10 minutes, flipping the bites halfway through cooking. For medium-rare bites, cook to an internal temperature of 135F.
Allow the bites to rest for 5 minutes. Toss with chimichurri and serve with bread. Enjoy!

Creator: kimthefoodie
Name: Steak Bites with Chimichurri (Air Fryer)
Description: These juicy steak bites are tossed in fresh chimichurri and are perfect for sharing!

directions.Direction: Preheat oven to 375F.
To a mixing bowl, add cream cheese, canned jalepeno peppers, 1 cup cheddar cheese, and most of the bacon. Set aside a small amount of bacon for sprinkling on the dip.
Stir to combine and spread dip into a small baking dish. Sprinkle with the remaining cheddar cheese, reserved bacon, and fresh jalepeno pepper.
Bake for 15 minutes or until the edges are bubbling.
Serve with tortilla chips and enjoy!

Creator: kimthefoodie
Name: Jalepeno Popper Dip
Description: A warm baked dip loaded with all the delicious flavors of jalepeno poppers!

directions.Direction: Heat 3/4 cup milk over medium until it starts to steam.
Whisk in the dark chocolate and sugar. Continue to stir until the chocolate melts.
In a small bowl, whisk together the remaining 1/4 cup milk and cornstarch. Add to the hot chocolate and stir occasionally until thickened.
Serve in a mug with whipped cream. Enjoy!

Creator: kimthefoodie
Name: Italian-style hot chocolate
Description: This one’s for the chocolate lovers! I adore tucking into a warm mug of Italian-style hot chocolate around the holidays. It’s thick, rich, and easier to make than you think!

ingredients.Name: All purpose flour, for dusting your work surface

directions.Direction: Preheat the air fryer to 400F.

Lightly dust your work surface with flour. Unroll the top and bottom pie crusts so they’re flat and cut them into smaller circles using a 4 to 5 inch cookie cutter. A large drinking glass works for this too! Gather the scraps of dough and re-roll them using a rolling pin. Cut out more circles and continue this process until you’ve used all the crust.
Spoon 1 to 2 tablespoons of Nutella into the center of each crust circle.

Whisk together the egg and water. Brush the mixture onto the exposed edges of each crust. Carefully fold the pies in half and seal them closed with your fingers. Use a fork to press a decorative edge into the round side of each pie.
Brush the tops of the pies with more egg wash. Cut 3 slits into the top-center of each one, being careful not to poke any holes into the bottom.
Place the hand pies in a single layer in your air fryer basket. You might have to work in batches. Air fry the pies for 7 to 10 minutes or until the tops are golden.
Allow the pies to cool for 5 minutes before eating. Enjoy!

Creator: kimthefoodie
Name: Air Fryer Nutella Hand Pies (Easy!)
Description:
These hand pies can be made quickly in the air fryer with only 5 ingredients (Pssstttt, one of them is water). 

Not a big fan of Nutella? Sub it out for your favorite pie filling!

directions.Direction: Prepare a 9x13x2 pan by lining it with parchment paper.
Pour the Mini Eggs into a large plastic freezer bag. Seal the bag shut while removing as much air as possible. Using a rolling pin, carefully crush the Mini Eggs into smaller pieces.
Melt the butter in a large pot on low heat. Add the marshmallows and stir occasionally until they're completely melted.
As soon as the marshmallows have melted, remove the pot from heat and stir in the Rice Krispies and two-thirds of the crushed Mini Eggs.
Pour the mixture into the prepared pan and spread it out using a spatula or wet fingers. Do your best to press the mixture down gently. If you pack down the squares too much, they won't be as soft!
Sprinkle the remaining Mini Eggs over top of the mixture and press them in gently so they stick.
Allow the mixture to cool and cut into 24 squares. Best enjoyed the same day - enjoy!

Creator: kimthefoodie
Name: Mini Egg Rice Krispie Treats
Description: Everyone's fave dessert bar with a Mini Egg twist!  I've refined my base recipe for Rice Krispie treats over the past couple of years, and I find that this method gives me the softest, chewiest result.

directions.Direction: Preheat oven to 350F.
In a large mixing bowl, use a spoon to combine the sugar and butter until smooth.
Add the flour and continue to stir until it's moistened throughout and has pea sized clumps.
Press the mixture into a 9"x13" rectangular baking dish.
Bake for 20 minutes. Set the cooked crust aside while you prepare the filling.

Creator: kimthefoodie
Name: Easy Lemon Squares
Description: I come back to this lemon square recipe so often because of how easy it is to throw together. You don't have to fuss with any special equipment and the gooey lemon filling is reminiscent of a fresh lemon pie.  Perfect as a warm weather dessert for a crowd!
